Reading guide
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────[0m

[2;37m# Three artifacts derive from one FMPL binding:[0m
[2;37m# 1. SOURCE  — the exact bytes the user typed (`\x x * x`).[0m
[2;37m# 2. VALUE   — the serialized runtime Value enum (JSON).[0m
[2;37m# 3. BYTECODE — the Lambda's CompiledCode (instructions + nested).[0m

[2;37m# Each goes into the same content-addressed SourceStore under its[0m
[2;37m# blake3 hash. The store doesn't know the kind — that lives only in[0m
[2;37m# the metadata `.store-*` prints.[0m

[2;37m# Two REPL processes (Alice, Bob) sequence through one store.[0m
[2;37m# Bob's recovery is byte-identical to Alice's input — that's the[0m
[2;37m# audit at the end.[0m

